# Copy to .env.harness (gitignored) in this repo root or under your AgentCore project
# (e.g. salesforceAgent00/.env.harness). Then: npm run merge-harness-env → agentcore deploy.
#
# This file is ONLY for Salesforce JWT vars pushed into harness.json. Slack tokens
# (SLACK_APP_TOKEN, SLACK_BOT_TOKEN) and HARNESS_ARN stay in .env — see README.md
# "Slack tokens and HARNESS_ARN".
#
# --- Option A: AWS at runtime (best for prod — no PEM in git / harness.json) ---
#
# Put this JSON in Secrets Manager or SSM Parameter Store (SecureString):
#   { "SF_LOGIN_URL":"https://login.salesforce.com","SF_CLIENT_ID":"…","SF_USERNAME":"…","SF_PRIVATE_KEY_BODY":"…" }
#
# Then set pointers only (merge copies these into harness.json / baked file):
#   SF_SECRET_ID=arn:aws:secretsmanager:us-west-2:123456789012:secret:name-xxxx   # OR name only in-region
#   # SF_SSM_PARAMETER_NAME=/salesforce-agent/jwt   # optional second fetch (JSON); merged after secret
# Omit SF_CLIENT_ID / SF_USERNAME / SF_PRIVATE_KEY_* below when using AWS-only.
#
# Do NOT use the Secrets Manager wizard template "Salesforce External Client App Credential"
# (consumerKey/consumerSecret/baseUri/...) — that is for a different OAuth flow. This repo
# needs JWT JSON with SF_* keys; use "Other type of secret". See docs/agentcore-harness.md §3A.
#
# IAM (harness execution role): secretsmanager:GetSecretValue on that secret; for SSM SecureString:
#   ssm:GetParameter + kms:Decrypt on the parameter's KMS key.
# AgentCore must set AWS_REGION (or set SF_AWS_REGION in harness env).
#
# --- Option B: Inline PEM (pick ONE approach for the key) ---
#
# 1) RECOMMENDED: SF_PRIVATE_KEY_BODY — only the base64 between PEM header lines, one line
#    (no -----BEGIN/END-----, no spaces or newlines inside the value).
#    From a PKCS#8 file (BEGIN PRIVATE KEY), in zsh/bash:
#      SF_PRIVATE_KEY_BODY=$(sed -n '/-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----/,/-----END PRIVATE KEY-----/p' key.pem | grep -v 'BEGIN\|END' | tr -d '[:space:]')
#    Then in .env.harness: SF_PRIVATE_KEY_BODY=$SF_PRIVATE_KEY_BODY   (or paste the string)
#    If your key is BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY, run: openssl pkcs8 -topk8 -nocrypt -in rsa.pem -out pk8.pem
#    and use pk8.pem in the sed above, or use SF_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE instead.
#
# 2) SF_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE — path to a .pem file (relative to this file or absolute).
#    Example: SF_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE=./connected-app-server.key
#
# 3) SF_PRIVATE_KEY — MUST be double-quoted if the PEM spans multiple lines, e.g.
#    SF_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
#    MIIE...
#    -----END PRIVATE KEY-----"
#    If you omit quotes, only the first line is read and deploy will break JWT auth.

SF_LOGIN_URL=https://login.salesforce.com
SF_CLIENT_ID=
SF_USERNAME=
# SF_PRIVATE_KEY=
# SF_PRIVATE_KEY_BODY=
# SF_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE=
#
# Optional: SF_QUERY_DEBUG=1 — sf-query writes [sf-query] JSON lines to stderr (lengths/stages only).
# Locally: npm run debug-sf-query. On the harness: merge + push-harness-env; logs appear where
# AgentCore surfaces tool stderr (often CloudWatch for the runtime / session — not the Bolt terminal).
# SF_QUERY_DEBUG=1
